description: Available at: https://openstudionetwork.com/keezer - One of the greatest recorded jazz piano solos of all time, Memphis pianist Phineas Newborn Jr.'s spellbinding take on Charlie Parker's blues "Cheryl" remains a benchmark to this day, and is a virtual master class in "block chord"-based improvisation. Geoffrey breaks two choruses down for you, measure by measure. (Note: Geoffrey recommends that you check out his video "Block Chords" before diving into this one!) (Level: Advanced)
fulltitle: Geoffrey Keezer - Phineas Newborn Jr.'s "Cheryl": A Study in Block Chords (Preview)
